# Resonance Foundation — Technical Framework (v2)

**Full rebuild** of the marketing site into a chapter-scoped nonprofit platform. Reuse copy/images from `oldcontent/`. Discord stays for internal officer/tutor coordination; in-app messaging is parent/student ↔ tutor ↔ chapter only.

## Stack

| Layer | Choice |
|---|---|
| App | Next.js (App Router), TypeScript, Tailwind, shadcn/ui |
| Host | Vercel (GitHub auto-deploy) |
| DB + Auth + Realtime | Supabase (RLS for chapter/role scoping) |
| Sensitive files | Supabase Storage (waivers, consent, minor PII) |
| General files | Google Drive links (sheet music, flyers, photos) |
| Email | Resend |
| PDFs | `@react-pdf/renderer` or `pdf-lib` |
| Payments | PayPal (donations; webhook TBD) |
| Calendar | FullCalendar (tutor availability, chapter calendar, events) |
| Charts / Tables | Recharts / TanStack Table |

## Roles (least → most privilege)

`Student/Parent` (chapter) · `Tutor` · `Volunteer/Performer` · `Chapter Officer` · `Chapter President` · `Corporate Officer` (org) · `Program Administrator` (org, audit write) · `Board of Director` (org, full)

**Student/Parent = one shared account.** Parent owns the login; multiple `students` can link to one parent. Any tutor→student message is visible to the parent by default — keep the UI honest (no implied private student inbox). One login per household, not per kid.

## Core schema

```
chapters · profiles (extends auth.users) · user_roles (user, chapter?, role, status)
students (parent_user_id, chapter_id, instrument, skill_level, financial_aid, status)
guardian_consents · applicants (recruitment pipeline → converted_user_id on activation)
tutor_availability · lessons · lesson_logs · practice_logs · assignments · resources
certificates · events · event_rsvps · event_attendance
volunteer_hours (category, status, approved_by) · donations · audit_logs
conversations · conversation_members · messages (soft-delete via deleted_at) · announcements · notifications
```

**Recruitment stages:** interested → applied → accepted → active → alumni. **Volunteer categories:** teaching · event_support · admin_work.

## RLS pattern

`get_user_roles(uid)` → `(role, chapter_id)` pairs; every policy checks against it.

| Role | Read | Write |
|---|---|---|
| Board | all | all |
| Program Admin | all | `audit_logs` only |
| Corporate Officer | org `events`, `donations` | same |
| Chapter President/Officer | own chapter | own chapter (+ approve `volunteer_hours`) |
| Tutor | assigned students, own threads | `lessons`, `lesson_logs`, `assignments`, `resources`, own hours |
| Student/Parent | own linked students | `practice_logs`, RSVPs, own messages |
| Volunteer/Performer | own chapter events | own `volunteer_hours` |

**Messaging safety (do not skip):** tutor↔student threads are auditable by that chapter's Officer/President and by Program Admin/Board. Messages are never hard-deleted — `deleted_at` hides from UI only. Parent visibility + officer audit = structural minor-safety safeguard.

## Storage

PII/signatures → Supabase Storage. Everything else → Drive link or small Supabase upload via `resources.storage_type` (`link` / `drive` / `supabase`).

## Feature → data map (quick ref)

- **Student:** upcoming `lessons`, history `lesson_logs`, `practice_logs`, `assignments`, `resources`, progress charts, `certificates`, tutor messaging
- **Tutor:** assigned students, `tutor_availability` + FullCalendar, schedule `lessons`, log attendance/notes, assign homework, upload resources, log hours
- **Chapter:** members via `students`/`user_roles`, chapter calendar (`lessons` + `events`), `applicants` pipeline, chapter docs, Recharts analytics
- **Events:** `events` + RSVP (`going`/`maybe`/`declined`), capacity enforced vs `event_rsvps`, `event_attendance`, email (Resend) + in-app `notifications`
- **Volunteer:** log → Officer approves → auto `certificates` + PDF export of approved hours
- **Admin:** org dashboard, `user_roles`, `chapters`, donation tracking, `audit_logs`

## Build phases

1. **Foundation** — Auth, chapters, profiles, roles, students (shared parent), RLS, enrollment + application forms → `applicants`
2. **Lessons** — lessons, logs, practice, assignments, resources, tutor + student dashboards
3. **Chapter ops** — events, RSVP, attendance, recruitment UI, docs, FullCalendar
4. **Volunteer** — approval workflow, certificates, PDF export
5. **Messaging** — conversations, messages, announcements, notifications + Realtime, audit rule
6. **Admin** — donations, audit expansion, global dashboard, analytics

## Open questions (confirm before building)

1. Officer/Admin/Board **read access** to tutor↔student threads (recommended default) — explicit sign-off wanted
2. Donations: manual entry first vs PayPal webhook auto-logging
3. Certificate template: generic PDF OK for v1?

## Conventions

- Scope all chapter data by `chapter_id`; org-wide rows use `chapter_id = null`
- Prefer server actions / API routes with Supabase service role only where RLS cannot apply
- Do not add features outside the current phase without user approval
- When adding tables/policies, update RLS in the same change
